{"link": "https://www.marketwatch.com/story/todays-research-reports-on-stocks-to-watch-broadcom-limited-and-nvidia-2018-02-06", "source": "https://www.marketwatch.com/", "text": "Published: Feb 06, 2018 (ACCESSWIRE via COMTEX) -- NEW YORK, NY / ACCESSWIRE / February 6, 2018 / Broadcom Limited really wants Qualcomm and the company proved that yesterday by upping their bid from $70 a share to $82 a share. NVIDIA announced a new partnership with Continental AG for self-driving. Despite both companies having exciting news, the market's downfall pushed these two stocks lower with it. RDI Initiates Coverage on: Broadcom Limited   NVIDIA Corporation   Broadcom's shares closed down 3.13% on about 7 million shares traded yesterday. The company has now offered more money for Qualcomm. The chipmaker is increasing the pressure on Qualcomm by sweetening its offer to $82 a share in cash and stock. Initially the company had offered $70 a share, or a value of $105 billion last November. The new offer is valuing Qualcomm at $121 billion. According to Drexel Hamilton analyst, Cody Acree, \"It's an aggressive bid for Qualcomm alone.\" Broadcom isn't however bidding just for Qualcomm. Qualcomm is expected to acquire NXP. Qualcomm's market price was close to $100 billion before it dropped yesterday, and NXP is valued at $40 billion. \"If you put those two together, you've got $140 billion of market cap on an aggregate basis,\" said Acree. Access RDI's Broadcom Limited Research Report at:   NVIDIA's shares closed down 8.49% on Monday. The stock was one of the biggest losers on the NASDAQ despite the company having some exciting news. NVIDIA announced a new partnership with Continental AG, a German auto company. Continental AG will be using the chipmaker's Drive platform to build a full-blown self driving vehicle system by 2021. NVIDIA CEO Jensen Huang commented, \"We now have all the key elements in place to take AI self-driving cars from development to mass production. Our newly arrived Drive Xavier processor, extensive Nvidia Drive software, and cloud-to-car approach for testing, validation and functional safety, combined with Continental's expertise and global reach, will bring autonomous cars to the world.\" Trading volume at 29 million shares yesterday was more than double the stock's average. Continental AG CEO Elmar Degenhart commented, \"The vehicle of the future will be a sensing, planning and acting computer on wheels. The complexity of autonomous driving requires nothing less than the full computational horsepower of an AI supercomputer. Together with the performance and flexibility of Nvidia's AI self-driving solution, from the cloud to the car we will achieve new levels of safety, comfort and personalization for future vehicles.\" Access RDI's NVIDIA Corporation Research Report at:   Our Actionable Research on Broadcom Limited and NVIDIA Corporation can be downloaded free of charge at Research Driven Investing. Research Driven Investing We are committed to providing relevant and actionable information for the self-directed investor. Our research is reputed for being a leader in trusted, in-depth analysis vital for informed strategic trading decisions. The nimble investor can leverage our analysis and collective expertise to execute a disciplined approach to stock selection. RDInvesting has not been compensated; directly or indirectly; for producing or publishing this document. Disclaimer: This article is written by an independent contributor of RDInvesting.com and Nadia Noorani, a CFA\u00ae charter holder, has provided necessary guidance in preparing the document templates. RDInvesting.com is neither a registered broker dealer nor a registered investment advisor. For more information please read our full disclaimer at . CONTACT For any questions, inquiries, or comments reach out to us directly at: Address: Research Driven Investing, Unit #901 511 Avenue of the Americas, New York, NY, 10011 Email: contact@rdinvesting.com CFA\u00ae and C